{
  "text": "It is important to consider the lack of significant association between DRD4 variants and ADHD in the recent large genome-wide association study [CITATION_1] , though some of the other affected loci (FOXP2, DUSP6) may have a role in synaptic dopamine regulation. It is also likely that the DRD4 polymorphism interacts with other genetic determinants of brain development, thus influencing the brain structure in ADHD. Larger genome-wide examination of the relationship between ADHD-related common variants and gyrification is needed to address this issue.",
